1
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:02,567
<i>I've been told that
you're flirting with a guest!</i>

2
00:00:02,667 --> 00:00:06,400
<i>I don't care if that's
what you do outside,</i>

3
00:00:06,567 --> 00:00:08,900
<i> but never do that in my hotel.</i>

4
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,933
<i> Don't talk to me like that.</i>

5
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:14,400
<i>We don't have time
for mixed signals anymore!</i>

6
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:16,733
<i>- If it's confusing...
- Mm-hm.</i>

7
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:18,567
<i>- I'll clear it up.
- Yes!</i>

8
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:20,133
<i> That's my girly pop.</i>

9
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:22,867
<i>What is this, a drama?
You're worlds apart?</i>

10
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:26,033
<i> Jade and I are just friends.</i>

11
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:27,800
<i> I only see her as a friend.</i>

12
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:29,967
<i> Why are you crying, Jade?</i>

13
00:00:30,833 --> 00:00:32,267
<i> Why did that hurt you?</i>

14
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:33,867
<i>How can I even compete
with Edward?</i>

15
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,800
<i>- Just look at me.
- You look dirty!</i>

16
00:00:35,967 --> 00:00:37,600
<i>I would like to use
my third wish.</i>

17
00:00:37,700 --> 00:00:39,100
<i> Let's do the prom again.</i>

18
00:00:43,867 --> 00:00:45,300
[JADE] Run away?

19
00:00:46,467 --> 00:00:49,267
The same place
where the prom was held?

20
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,133
[CHUCKLES]

21
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:54,900
But isn't your entire problem
that I stood you up?

22
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,900
Why did you take me here again?

23
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,733
Is this a punishment?

24
00:00:58,833 --> 00:01:01,300
No. It's not a punishment.

25
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:07,067
Honestly, this place is nice.

26
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:11,633
Unfortunately, we have
some bad memories in here.

27
00:01:12,967 --> 00:01:14,033
Right?

28
00:01:14,167 --> 00:01:15,633
But I thought,

29
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,167
let's change that.

30
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:19,767
Let's do the prom again.

31
00:01:19,867 --> 00:01:21,033
Edward...

32
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:22,533
Come on, Jade.

33
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:25,467
So, the next time someone asks,

34
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:28,800
we can say, "Yes!

35
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:33,600
We went on a prom date."

36
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,633
Okay, fine.

37
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:43,167
Since this is your wish.

38
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:45,167
But wait, how will we--

39
00:01:45,267 --> 00:01:47,833
Don't worry.
I prepared everything.

40
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:51,367
I've prepared a dress for you
in the room.

41
00:01:55,167 --> 00:01:56,567
So, see you later?

42
00:01:59,033 --> 00:02:05,833
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:02:16,067 --> 00:02:22,900
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

44
00:02:38,067 --> 00:02:44,867
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

45
00:03:00,067 --> 00:03:06,900
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

46
00:03:18,967 --> 00:03:20,800
Justin...

47
00:03:20,967 --> 00:03:23,000
I'm sorry.

48
00:03:23,133 --> 00:03:25,833
I didn't mean what I said.

49
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:30,733
She really said it
word-for-word.

50
00:03:32,167 --> 00:03:34,500
At least, do it right.

51
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,900
So...

52
00:03:42,033 --> 00:03:43,300
Are we good now?

53
00:03:43,467 --> 00:03:45,933
We can talk about the bar?

54
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:48,667
What?

55
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:52,600
Are you only apologizing
because you need something?

56
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:54,133
Yeah-- no!

57
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:56,300
No. I-- I mean...

58
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:59,133
Yes, I'm sorry.

59
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:00,267
And yes, I need something--

60
00:04:00,367 --> 00:04:02,833
Can't you apologize sincerely?

61
00:04:05,067 --> 00:04:07,833
But I said sorry.

62
00:04:08,900 --> 00:04:10,300
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

63
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,933
And I say...

64
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:13,833
no!

65
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:16,167
And no,
we can't talk about the bar.

66
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:17,667
And that's sincere.

67
00:04:19,033 --> 00:04:21,967
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYS]

68
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:32,200
[KIKO] I have to apologize.

69
00:04:32,367 --> 00:04:35,033
<i>It's not her fault
that I'm a coward.</i>

70
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:43,900
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN PLAYING]

71
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:05,900
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN CONTINUES]

72
00:05:21,367 --> 00:05:24,033
<i> If he can't say his feelings,</i>

73
00:05:24,133 --> 00:05:26,700
<i> I'll say mine.</i>

74
00:05:26,867 --> 00:05:29,267
<i> Jade and I are just friends.</i>

75
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,200
<i> I only see her as a friend.</i>

76
00:05:40,633 --> 00:05:42,533
[EDWARD] I want you to be free.

77
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:44,733
<i>So, you're going
to run away with me.</i>

78
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:47,400
<i> A vacation?</i>

79
00:05:48,133 --> 00:05:51,933
<i>So you can get rid
of that negative energy.</i>

80
00:05:56,967 --> 00:06:03,900
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN CONTINUES]

81
00:06:13,167 --> 00:06:14,767
[EDWARD]
<i> She's probably getting ready.</i>

82
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,933
[MUSIC FADES]

83
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,167
Kiko.

84
00:06:36,667 --> 00:06:39,133
- Martin.
- Waiting for someone?

85
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:40,933
Yes. Jade.

86
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:42,167
Jade?

87
00:06:43,467 --> 00:06:45,333
Has she come in?

88
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,767
No.

89
00:06:46,867 --> 00:06:50,167
Luna said she's handling Jade's
responsibilities for now.

90
00:06:50,333 --> 00:06:52,033
She's in some sort of leave.

91
00:06:52,167 --> 00:06:53,633
Leave?

92
00:06:53,733 --> 00:06:56,133
Why? Did anything happen?

93
00:06:56,233 --> 00:06:58,533
That's all they said.

94
00:06:58,667 --> 00:07:01,267
Don't look for something
that won't come.

95
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:11,300
[KIKO]<i> "I didn't see you
</i> at the hotel the whole day.

96
00:07:11,467 --> 00:07:13,767
<i> Martin said you're on leave.</i>

97
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:16,867
<i> Are you okay?"</i>

98
00:07:19,033 --> 00:07:26,000
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN CONTINUES]

99
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:38,000
[MUSIC ENDS]

100
00:07:38,567 --> 00:07:40,500
Hey. You.

101
00:07:40,667 --> 00:07:42,500
What was that?

102
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,500
I swear to god,
you're hopeless.

103
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,700
That's the biggest fail
I've seen in my life.

104
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:49,633
Might as well
not apologize at all.

105
00:07:49,767 --> 00:07:52,733
You've recited it
word-for-word,

106
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:55,033
and yet,
you still messed it up.

107
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,833
But I said it, didn't I?

108
00:07:56,933 --> 00:07:59,100
What else does he want?

109
00:07:59,233 --> 00:08:00,700
Sure, you did.

110
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:03,200
But you brought up the bar
right after.

111
00:08:03,367 --> 00:08:04,867
You're obviously
just apologizing

112
00:08:05,033 --> 00:08:07,033
because you need something.

113
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,167
Goodness.

114
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:09,433
[GROANS]

115
00:08:09,567 --> 00:08:12,200
Why is it so hard to apologize?

116
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:15,233
Wanna know why?

117
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:18,733
Because an apology

118
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:22,367
is for the person who got hurt.

119
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:25,433
You're apologizing because
you care about their feelings,

120
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,300
and you're
making it up to them.

121
00:08:28,967 --> 00:08:32,067
But you're only
apologizing for yourself.

122
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,300
Am I right or am I right?

123
00:08:36,633 --> 00:08:38,900
You should've
told me that earlier.

124
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,233
So, I'm still wrong.

125
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:43,467
Wow. Now, it's my fault.

126
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,300
[GROANS] Fine!

127
00:08:45,433 --> 00:08:47,400
Fine. Okay.

128
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:48,533
[SIGHS]

129
00:08:48,633 --> 00:08:51,067
Let's look for Justin. Come on.

130
00:08:51,767 --> 00:08:53,300
I want an apology, too.

131
00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:54,467
Yes! I'm sorry!

132
00:08:54,633 --> 00:08:56,067
I'm hurt, too!

133
00:09:01,967 --> 00:09:08,967
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

134
00:09:23,967 --> 00:09:30,933
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

135
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:37,267
[JUAN] Hotel 88's map.

136
00:09:37,367 --> 00:09:38,800
<i> And the treasure...</i>

137
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:43,800
I knew it's somewhere in there.

138
00:09:47,967 --> 00:09:54,967
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

139
00:10:04,533 --> 00:10:05,367
[PHONE DINGS]

140
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:08,533
[JUAN] "Let's meet up.

141
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:10,333
<i> We need to talk."</i>

142
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,333
I need to talk to him.

143
00:10:17,433 --> 00:10:19,133
Who? The man?

144
00:10:19,233 --> 00:10:21,333
Yes, the man.

145
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:23,500
But where did he go?

146
00:10:23,667 --> 00:10:25,400
Is that Justin?

147
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:30,900
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

148
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,167
- Over there.
- Oh, yeah.

149
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,833
- Justin?
- Justin!

150
00:10:35,933 --> 00:10:37,833
- Yeah, it's him!
- [CHESKA] Justin!

151
00:10:37,933 --> 00:10:41,067
- Justin!
- [TRIXIE] Justin, wait up!

152
00:10:41,233 --> 00:10:43,367
Justin, wait!

153
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:47,667
- He's gone.
- [PANTING]

154
00:10:47,767 --> 00:10:50,233
Let's... Let's hail a tricycle.

155
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,500
Mister!

156
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:54,533
Mister, hello. Good evening.

157
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:56,533
- Let's follow that car.
- What?

158
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:59,367
We need to follow Justin.
Come on!

159
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:01,100
I really need to talk to him.

160
00:11:03,567 --> 00:11:05,167
Let's hurry, please.

161
00:11:09,233 --> 00:11:10,933
Sir, we're not open yet.

162
00:11:11,067 --> 00:11:13,300
No, I'm just here
to see a friend.

163
00:11:13,433 --> 00:11:14,300
Okay.

164
00:11:16,633 --> 00:11:18,967
[BOUNCER] Hey, Gio!
It's been a long time!

165
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:21,067
- How are you?
- What brings you here?

166
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:25,200
I need to ask you something.

167
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:27,267
Do you know Peter Montevilla?

168
00:11:28,167 --> 00:11:29,533
Is this about Solenn?

169
00:11:30,667 --> 00:11:31,267
Mm.

170
00:11:31,433 --> 00:11:33,300
That was a long time ago,
Gio.

171
00:11:36,467 --> 00:11:37,233
Bro, please.

172
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,633
I need to know
his connection to Solenn.

173
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:41,033
Tsk.

174
00:11:42,133 --> 00:11:43,233
All I know is...

175
00:11:43,367 --> 00:11:44,900
they used to be
in a relationship.

176
00:11:45,033 --> 00:11:46,400
They were on and off.

177
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:51,067
But Peter really loved her.

178
00:11:51,167 --> 00:11:53,067
He adored Solenn.

179
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,567
Does he still come here?

180
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:56,767
Gio...

181
00:11:56,933 --> 00:11:58,967
I need to confirm something.

182
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:03,667
Actually,
he has a reservation tonight.

183
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:10,600
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:21,633
[ENGINE HUMMING, SHUTS OFF]

185
00:12:24,367 --> 00:12:32,300
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

186
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,933
- [CHESKA] Hey, friend!
- What the?

187
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:38,300
What are you doing here?

188
00:12:38,467 --> 00:12:40,767
What are you doing here?
This place is so scary!

189
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:42,633
- Why are you--
- Cheska!

190
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,767
No, uh, we're here because...

191
00:12:44,867 --> 00:12:46,433
Trixie wants to talk to you.

192
00:12:46,533 --> 00:12:48,000
Now?

193
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:49,800
You left all of a sudden,
Justin.

194
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:51,133
I know you'd ignore my texts,

195
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:53,633
so I told Cheska
we should follow you.

196
00:12:53,733 --> 00:12:55,200
Go back to the hotel!

197
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:58,467
Wait, Justin!
Talk to me!

198
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:00,300
Please, Justin!

199
00:13:03,033 --> 00:13:08,800
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

200
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:10,333
[EXCLAIMS]
Let me go!

201
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:12,033
- Let me go!
- [BLOW LANDS]

202
00:13:12,167 --> 00:13:14,967
- [JUAN GRUNTS]
- [BLOW, KICK LAND]

203
00:13:15,067 --> 00:13:16,467
- [BODY THUDS]
- [JUAN GRUNTS]

204
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,733
- [ASSAILANT 2 GRUNTS]
- [JUAN EXCLAIMS]

205
00:13:18,867 --> 00:13:20,167
[BLOWS LAND]

206
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:23,067
- [THUD]
- [BLOWS LAND]

207
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,433
[JUAN GRUNTING]

208
00:13:25,567 --> 00:13:27,400
- [BODY THUDS]
- [WOOD CLATTERS]

209
00:13:28,733 --> 00:13:30,333
[JUAN GRUNTS WEAKLY]

210
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:35,100
- [ASSAILANT 1 GRUNTS]
- [VASE SHATTERS]

211
00:13:36,467 --> 00:13:37,833
[BODY THUDS]

212
00:13:37,967 --> 00:13:40,033
[GRUNTS] Get him!

213
00:13:41,633 --> 00:13:43,500
[BOTH GRUNT]

214
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:48,667
Come on.

215
00:13:48,767 --> 00:13:51,167
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

216
00:13:51,267 --> 00:13:53,100
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

217
00:13:53,233 --> 00:13:55,333
Hide! Hide! Hide!

218
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:57,867
Get down, get down.

219
00:13:57,967 --> 00:14:03,867
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

220
00:14:03,967 --> 00:14:04,900
Juan?

221
00:14:05,067 --> 00:14:07,633
Where are they taking him?

222
00:14:10,067 --> 00:14:11,867
- Come on!
- Hurry!

223
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,533
- Get in!
- What the hell?

224
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:16,733
Oh! Go, go!

225
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:18,533
Hurry, hide!

226
00:14:18,633 --> 00:14:20,367
Over there!

227
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:26,867
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

228
00:14:26,967 --> 00:14:30,433
[PHONE BUZZING]

229
00:14:33,667 --> 00:14:34,733
Hello, boss?

230
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:36,233
We have Juan.

231
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:42,733
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

232
00:14:42,833 --> 00:14:43,733
Come on, let's go.

233
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:46,733
[ENGINE REVS]

234
00:14:46,867 --> 00:14:53,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

235
00:14:53,767 --> 00:15:00,733
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

236
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:14,767
[WHISPERS] Peter's upstairs.

237
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:26,467
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

238
00:15:32,133 --> 00:15:34,133
[GLASSES CLINK]

239
00:15:36,367 --> 00:15:38,167
Gio's here.

240
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:46,367
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

241
00:15:57,533 --> 00:16:04,533
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

242
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:11,900
[CHASE]
<i> The truth hurts, huh?</i>

243
00:16:12,033 --> 00:16:12,833
<i> It stings.</i>

244
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:14,933
<i>Especially  since
Peter is your ex!</i>

245
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,900
<i> Enough, Chase!</i>

246
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:20,233
<i>You had the best time with
your ex, who's a drug addict!</i>

247
00:16:22,467 --> 00:16:24,433
[GIO]
<i> What did you do to Luna?</i>

248
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:31,567
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:16:39,133 --> 00:16:46,100
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

250
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:49,600
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

251
00:16:52,900 --> 00:16:54,567
Sir, Ms. Jade really isn't
responding.

252
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:56,100
We've been calling her
for a while now.

253
00:16:57,633 --> 00:16:58,667
[SIGHS]

254
00:16:58,667 --> 00:17:00,733
Alright. Thank you. [SNIFFLES]

255
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,733
[EDWARD CLEARS THROAT]

256
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:06,867
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

257
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:11,200
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

258
00:17:17,367 --> 00:17:24,300
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

259
00:17:38,867 --> 00:17:45,767
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

260
00:17:58,167 --> 00:17:59,600
One last...

261
00:18:08,333 --> 00:18:15,267
["PANGHABANG IKAW" BY DARREN
ESPANTO PLAYING]

262
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:31,967
Sorry...

263
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:33,533
I'm late.

264
00:18:38,233 --> 00:18:39,700
May I have this dance?

265
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:46,667
["PANGHABANG IKAW" BY DARREN
ESPANTO CONTINUES]

266
00:19:01,767 --> 00:19:08,733
["PANGHABANG IKAW" BY DARREN
ESPANTO CONTINUES]

267
00:19:23,767 --> 00:19:30,733
["PANGHABANG IKAW" BY DARREN
ESPANTO CONTINUES]

268
00:19:45,167 --> 00:19:46,800
I have already updated
the department heads

269
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,633
about the report
you were asking for.

270
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:51,933
Okay.

271
00:19:52,267 --> 00:19:53,100
Is there anything else?

272
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:54,433
Yes, sir.

273
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:58,867
[FOLDER RUSTLING]

274
00:19:59,433 --> 00:20:03,433
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

275
00:20:03,467 --> 00:20:04,500
You're quitting?

276
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:06,267
Effective immediately.

277
00:20:06,267 --> 00:20:07,367
Irrevocable?

278
00:20:07,367 --> 00:20:08,500
Definitely.

279
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:10,967
Is this about the guest?
Because--

280
00:20:10,967 --> 00:20:12,767
It's about a lot
of things, sir.

281
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:15,767
But an employee
is in no way obligated

282
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:17,233
to explain
why they're quitting.

283
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:19,300
We're professionals, aren't we?

284
00:20:21,867 --> 00:20:23,333
Excuse me, sir.

285
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:30,267
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

286
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:42,533
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:20:42,533 --> 00:20:45,800
[PHONE VIBRATING]

288
00:20:48,067 --> 00:20:49,333
Where are you?

289
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:51,433
I'm already inside.

290
00:20:51,967 --> 00:20:53,467
[VITO ON PHONE]
<i> I'm almost there.</i>

291
00:20:59,167 --> 00:21:06,033
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

292
00:21:20,167 --> 00:21:27,000
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

293
00:21:41,067 --> 00:21:47,900
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

294
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:08,933
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

295
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,633
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

296
00:22:26,733 --> 00:22:29,133
[LEON]<i> Do you know someone
</i> named Sandro Soliman?

297
00:22:29,933 --> 00:22:31,367
<i>I think I've heard
that name before.</i>

298
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:32,800
<i> Actually, from your dad.</i>

299
00:22:32,933 --> 00:22:35,700
<i>You only heard it from Dad?
You don't know him personally?</i>

300
00:22:35,833 --> 00:22:36,700
<i> No, no.</i>

301
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,900
<i>We were talking about
one of his business ventures</i>

302
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:43,133
<i>that he was planning to enter,
and that name came up.</i>

303
00:22:43,267 --> 00:22:45,267
<i>Did this Sandro guy
contact you?</i>

304
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:51,467
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

305
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,567
Sir, he's upstairs.

306
00:22:53,667 --> 00:22:54,667
Good.

307
00:23:06,433 --> 00:23:13,500
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

308
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,500
[JUAN] Who's in there?

309
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:19,667
Hey, let me go!

310
00:23:19,833 --> 00:23:21,167
Cowards!

311
00:23:21,433 --> 00:23:22,833
Fight me fair and square!

312
00:23:23,967 --> 00:23:25,367
Hey, who are you?

313
00:23:25,533 --> 00:23:26,667
Show yourself!

314
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:28,700
Who are you? Huh?

315
00:23:28,833 --> 00:23:30,467
Speak!

316
00:23:31,300 --> 00:23:32,333
Let me go!

317
00:23:32,467 --> 00:23:37,967
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

318
00:23:39,233 --> 00:23:41,333
[BLOWS LANDING]

319
00:23:42,333 --> 00:23:44,367
<i>That's him, right?
He's the man who took Juan.</i>

320
00:23:44,500 --> 00:23:46,267
<i>We can't report this.
We'll be in danger.</i>

321
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:48,033
<i> What happened to him?</i>

322
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:51,000
<i> He hasn't replied to my texts.</i>

323
00:23:51,133 --> 00:23:54,500
<i>And that only means nothing
can stop my plans anymore.</i>

324
00:23:54,633 --> 00:23:56,467
<i>He's been friends with Dad
for a long time,</i>

325
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,067
<i>but they've never done
business together.</i>

326
00:23:58,233 --> 00:24:00,633
<i>He's the one we need.
We're going to get him.</i>

327
00:24:00,767 --> 00:24:02,200
<i> Are you going to invest?</i>

328
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:03,400
<i> We'll discuss this over lunch.</i>

329
00:24:03,533 --> 00:24:04,733
And don't forget to bring Sari.

330
00:24:04,900 --> 00:24:06,733
<i>I want to stay here
at Hotel 88.</i>

331
00:24:07,067 --> 00:24:08,200
<i> What are you doing here?</i>
